					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12547476#post-4370164</guid>
				<title>Junior Staff - Site Criticism</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12547476/scp-4693#post-4370164</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 20 Sep 2019 22:34:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tanhony</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>776854</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really enjoyed this!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Tanhony&nbsp;rambles</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;TURN&nbsp;IT&nbsp;OFF</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Notably, SCP-4693-1 seem incapable of chirping as per typical of chicks of this age, instead, making a low-pitched grunting noise.</p> </blockquote> <p>This is a nice disconcerting little detail, and the mental image of these things grunting while performing gymnastics is just fantastic.</p> <blockquote> <p>Later revealed to be Portuguese: &quot;Run brothers!&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>Oh my god, this is incredible. I don’t know about other readers, but from the previous mention of ‘Chicken Brothers’ I was expecting some bizarre chicken-obsessed organization was doing this for nebulous reasons - a kind of thing that’s been done a lot - but the twist that the chickens themselves are behind it is really well-executed.</p> <blockquote> <p>&quot;Sorry for the trouble ~ Mama&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>Things like this - where we hint at a bigger story behind the smaller anomaly that we can find - is always something I really enjoy in skips, and this is no exception.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Funny, interesting and just really well-written - it’s a definite +1 from me!</p> <p><sub><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" >Tanhony</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</sub></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
